entries.title: Thousands of Israelis Protest Netanyahu Government's Judicial Overhaul Plans
entries.description: The newly sworn-in ruling coalition has vowed to curb the judiciary’s power.

entries.title: Ex-Bolsonaro Minister Arrested in Probe Over Brazil Riots
entries.description: The official in charge of the capital’s security at the time of Sunday’s riots surrendered to police as judicial authorities investigate what they say are a web of suspects intent on overthrowing the president.

entries.title: U.K. and EU Look to Mend Rift and Resolve Northern Ireland Trade Dispute
entries.description: The Ukraine war is bringing the sides closer and British support for Brexit seems to be weakening.

entries.title: Two Waves of Missile Attacks Rock Ukrainian Cities
entries.description: Some Ukrainian officials think Moscow might have used ballistic missiles, which Ukraine’s current air defenses can’t intercept.

entries.title: Turkey's Approval of Sweden, Finland NATO Membership Could Take Months
entries.description: The Turkish government is unlikely to seek parliamentary approval for Ankara to back the alliance’s expansion before a national election later this year, a presidential aide said.

entries.title: China Says 60,000 Have Died of Covid Since Controls Were Lifted
entries.description: Report marks first time Beijing has accounted for the toll of the current Omicron wave.

entries.title: Iran Hangs Alireza Akbari, Former Defense Official Accused of Spying
entries.description: The U.K. condemns the execution of the Iranian-British dual national as a politically motivated barbaric act.

entries.title: How Europe Escaped a Looming Energy Crisis
entries.description: The worst-case scenario has been averted through conservation by consumers, mild temperatures and a scramble to create more gas supplies.

entries.title: Brazilian Prosecutors Call for Probe of Former President Bolsonaro Over Riots
entries.description: Prosecutors accuse Jair Bolsonaro of spending years sowing distrust in the country’s electoral system.
